[size=130][u]Usage[/u][/size]

[size=125][u]Creating a POI on the map[/u][/size]

To create a [b]POI[/b] on the map, simply open the holomap, right-click on any location and select [b]Create POI at ...[/b] from the context menu. A new POI will be created at the selected location with a default name based on the coordinates.

[spoiler][img]https://raw.githubusercontent.com/chemodun/X4-PlayerPOI/refs/heads/main/docs/images/create_poi_on_map_at_any_point.png[/img][/spoiler]

The created [b]POI[/b] will be visible on the map and in the [b]Player POI[/b] tab of the Property Owned Information, where you can manage it (like renaming or self-destructing it) using the context menu.

[spoiler][img]https://raw.githubusercontent.com/chemodun/X4-PlayerPOI/refs/heads/main/docs/images/created_poi_at_point_on_map.png[/img][/spoiler]

Additionally, you can assign a [b]POI[/b] to an object on the map (like a station or a gate) by right-clicking on the object and selecting [b]Assign POI[/b] from the context menu. The [b]POI[/b] will be created and automatically located near the object, and its name will be generated based on the object's name.

Context menu for assigning a [b]POI[/b] to an object on the map is exactly the same as in space, see the next section for details.

[size=125][u]Creating a POI in space[/u][/size]

In space, you can only assign a [b]POI[/b] to an object (like a station or a gate) by right-clicking on the object and selecting [b]Assign POI[/b] from the context menu. The [b]POI[/b] will be created and automatically located near the object, and its name will be generated based on the object's name.

[spoiler][img]https://raw.githubusercontent.com/chemodun/X4-PlayerPOI/refs/heads/main/docs/images/assign_poi_on_object_in_space.png[/img][/spoiler]

The created [b]POI[/b] will be visible in space, on a map and in the [b]Player POI[/b] tab of the Property Owned Information, where you can manage it (like renaming or self-destructing it) using the context menu.

[spoiler][img]https://raw.githubusercontent.com/chemodun/X4-PlayerPOI/refs/heads/main/docs/images/poi_assigned_on_object_in_space.png[/img][/spoiler]

[size=125][u]Managing POIs[/u][/size]

You can manage your created [b]POIs[/b] in space, on map and in the [b]Player POI[/b] tab of the Property Owned Information.
All management actions (like renaming or self-destructing a [b]POI[/b]) are available in the context menu, which can be accessed by right-clicking on a [b]POI[/b] in space, on the map or in the tab.

[size=120][u]Managing POIs in space[/u][/size]

There is how the context menu for a [b]POI[/b] in space looks like:

[spoiler][img]https://raw.githubusercontent.com/chemodun/X4-PlayerPOI/refs/heads/main/docs/images/poi_context_menu_in_space.png[/img][/spoiler]

[size=115][u]Renaming a POI in space[/u][/size]

When you select "Rename" from the context menu of a [b]POI[/b] in space, a rename window will open, allowing you to enter a new name for the [b]POI[/b].

[spoiler][img]https://raw.githubusercontent.com/chemodun/X4-PlayerPOI/refs/heads/main/docs/images/poi_rename_in_space.png[/img][/spoiler]

As soon as you enter a new name and confirm it, the [b]POI[/b] will be renamed.

[spoiler][img]https://raw.githubusercontent.com/chemodun/X4-PlayerPOI/refs/heads/main/docs/images/poi_renamed_in_space.png[/img][/spoiler]

[size=120][u]Managing POIs on the map[/u][/size]

Context menu for a [b]POI[/b] on the map is the same as in space, but with an additional option to center the map on the [b]POI[/b]:

[spoiler][img]https://raw.githubusercontent.com/chemodun/X4-PlayerPOI/refs/heads/main/docs/images/poi_context_menu_on_map.png[/img][/spoiler]

[size=120][u]Managing POIs in the Player POI tab[/u][/size]

There is an additional tab in the Property Owned Information called [b]Player POI[/b], where you can see all your created [b]POIs[/b] in one place. You can also manage your [b]POIs[/b] from this tab using the same context menu as in space and on the map.

[spoiler][img]https://raw.githubusercontent.com/chemodun/X4-PlayerPOI/refs/heads/main/docs/images/poi_tab_in_property_owned.png[/img][/spoiler]

[size=115][u]Self-destructing a POI[/u][/size]

When you select "Self-destruct" from the context menu of a [b]POI[/b], the [b]POI[/b] will be immediately removed from the game. This action cannot be undone, so use it with caution.
There  is an example of a [b]POI[/b] that is about to be self-destructed in the following screenshot:

