[size=125][u]Options[/u][/size]

You can configure the mod in the options menu, which can be accessed from the [b]Player POI[/b] item in [b]Extension Options[/b]  menu.

[spoiler][img]https://raw.githubusercontent.com/chemodun/X4-PlayerPOI/refs/heads/main/docs/images/extension_options.png[/img][/spoiler]

Where the [b]Player POI[/b] options menu looks like this:

[spoiler][img]https://raw.githubusercontent.com/chemodun/X4-PlayerPOI/refs/heads/main/docs/images/poi_options.png[/img][/spoiler]

[size=120][u]Automatic POI assignment[/u][/size]

There are two options group under the [b]Automatic POI assignment when:[/b] section:
[list]
[*] [b]Found an abandoned ship[/b] - when enabled, a [b]POI[/b] will be automatically assigned to any found abandoned ship. But moreover, all already known abandoned ships will be assigned with [b]POI[/b]s on enabling this option.
[/list]
  This option has an additional sub-option [b]Only if no claim procedure is initiated[/b], which will only assign [b]POI[/b]s to abandoned ships that are not currently being claimed by player. This means that if the player set a claim procedure on an abandoned ship as default action or selected this action by event menu, the [b]POI[/b] will not be assigned to such ship.
[list]
[*] [b]Found a lockbox[/b] - when enabled, a [b]POI[/b] will be automatically assigned to any found lockbox. And similarly to previous, all already known lockboxes will be assigned with [b]POI[/b]s on enabling this option.
[/list]
[size=120][u]Other[/u][/size]

In this section, you can enable or disable [b]optimized[/b] rename window location, which will make the rename window appear near the selected [b]POI[/b] instead of the last mouse position.

There are two screenshots showing the difference between [b]optimized[/b] and [b]standard[/b] rename window location:
